I""<h1 id="tprcb">TPRCB</h1>
<p>Toilet Paper Roll Counter Box</p>

<h2 id="why">Why</h2>
<p>As I was sitting on the toilet the other day, I discovered we had no toilet paper left. Luckily I survived the event, but figured that this could never happen again!</p>

<p>Therefore I made a box that counts the number of toilet paper rolls, which also warns me if weâ€™re running low. Everything done with the help from <a href="https://www.home-assistant.io/">Home Assistant</a> and <a href="https://esphome.io/">ESPHome</a> ðŸŽ‰ðŸ¤©</p>

<p><img src="https://github.com/petrepa/TPRCB/blob/master/Photos/box.jpeg" alt="box" /></p>

<p>If we have less than 4 rolls, we get a subtle warning from the box
<img src="https://github.com/petrepa/TPRCB/blob/master/Photos/warning.gif" alt="warning" /></p>

<p>And if we have less than 2(!) rolls left, the box goes into EMERGENCY modeðŸš¨ðŸš¨ðŸš¨
<img src="https://github.com/petrepa/TPRCB/blob/master/Photos/emergency.gif" alt="emergency" /></p>

<h2 id="build">Build</h2>
<p>Built this using:</p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="http://www.nodemcu.com/index_en.html">NodeMCU</a> V3</li>
  <li>HX711 and a load cell</li>
  <li>Gilde Box (any see through plate would suffice)</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.clasohlson.com/no/Trekasse-med-h%C3%A5ndtak/Pr441449000">Clas Ohlson Wooden Box</a></li>
  <li>12V PSU</li>
  <li>Barrel Socket</li>
  <li>WS2812 LED Strip</li>
</ul>

